---
title: Flatbread Fattoush Salad with Crispy Chickpeas and Garlic Oil
description: It doesn’t matter if your favorite part of salad is the fresh veggies or the crispy croutons. Fattoush will satisfy either way. The Lebanese dish features both a jumble of greens, cucumbers, tomatoes, and chickpeas as wells as chunks of toasted bread. We’ll be using pieces of flatbread here, which soak up the dressing and have a dusting of herby za’atar, which adds plenty of vibrant flavor.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w10-r08-37be2111.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w10-r08-9d181f9b.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/flatbread-fattoush-salad-588bad71b32fbe6c113be492
cuisine: Lebanese
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Slice @green olives{1}(sliced crosswise). Slice @Persian cucumber{2}(sliced into thin rounds). Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}(halved lengthwise). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}(thinly sliced crosswise). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%box}.

On a #baking sheet{}, toss chickpeas, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Bake in oven until crisp, about ~{20%minutes}.

> Chickpeas may pop in oven—it's natural.

Heat @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until it just begins to brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, remove garlic from pan and discard.

With about ~{10%minutes} left on chickpeas, cut @flatbreads{2} into 1-inch squares. Toss in a #medium bowl{} with @za'atar spice{2%teaspoon} and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Add to baking sheet with chickpeas and carefully spread out. Return sheet to oven and continue baking until flatbread is toasty and crisp, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Whisk @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} into pan with garlic oil. Season with salt and pepper. Once chickpeas and flatbread are done, remove from oven and set aside to cool for a few minutes. Transfer to a #large bowl{}.

Add cucumber, olives, tomatoes, and as much shallot as you like to same bowl. Drizzle with vinaigrette (to taste) and toss thoroughly to coat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Divide between bowls, then sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}.

> TIP: If salad seems dry, add more olive oil.